/coastal scrubs, golf courses, vineyards, suburban streets and arid areas of Australia. They make a 'tchip-tchip' call similar to masked woodswallows. Reproduction Breeding occurs between August and December or after rain. The species nests in shrubs, forks of trees, hollow stumps or posts, the nest is usually made of twigs, grass and rootlets. The eggs are white/grey, spotted, or blotched brown-grey. A clutch will usually consist of 2 to 3 eggs. Diet White-browed woodswallows feed on nectar when blossoms are available but mainly feed on insects. References External links ABID Images Archived 2011-05-14 at the Wayback Machine White-browed woodswallow videos, photos & sounds on the Internet Bird Collection", "shortSummary": "The white-browed woodswallow (Artamus superciliosus) is a medium-sized (~19 cm) passerine bird endemic to Australia. The white-browed woods…", "locations": ["约翰·古尔德", "北領地"], "lat": -25.0, "lng": 133.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Artamus_superciliosus_male_2_-_Bushells_Lagoon.jpg/960px-Artamus_superciliosus_male_2_-_Bushells_Lagoon.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-artamus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-artamus-superciliosus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-artamus", "species": "taxonomy-species-artamus-superciliosus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 201.42, "y": -854.79, "z": 247.83}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-artamus", "name": "Artamus", "latinName": "Artamus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Artamus（Artamus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联11种鸟类，如灰燕鵙、Fiji woodswallow、Ivory-backed woodswallow等11种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 11, "x": -4.41, "y": -624.27, "z": -86.28}], "links": [{"key": "bird-white-browed-woodswallow-a39a7e9d__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-s